OL,6,FThe officer in charge of the
OL,7,Finvestigation, Detective Constable
OL,8,FCaroline Foord, said: "This case
OL,9,Fhighlights the serious nature of an
OL,10,Fabuse of authority and the importance
OL,11,Fof holding individuals accountable for
OL,12,Ftheir actions, regardless of their
OL,13,Fposition or standing in the community
OL,14,For when the offences were committed.
OL,16,F"Glas used his position, as an
OL,17,Finfluential member of the Catholic
OL,18,FClergy, to groom his victim and others
OL,19,Fwho trusted him. His offending
OL,20,Fbehaviours were both manipulative and
OL,21,Fcontrolling in nature.
